Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.37,0:00:07.64,SU,,0,0,0,,翻校 Husky
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.64,0:00:10.70,SU,,0,0,0,,资源 yoyo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.71,0:00:12.97,SU,,0,0,0,,压制 依依
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.29,0:00:28.72,SU,,0,0,0,,不能再美!\N{\fs48}It's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.72,0:00:31.63,SU,,0,0,0,,雪一直在下啊下的\N{\fs48}The snow just keeps falling and falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.63,0:00:34.06,SU,,0,0,0,,我很开心你能和我们住在一起,老爸\N{\fs48}I'm glad you're staying here with us, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.06,0:00:35.94,SU,,0,0,0,,我也很高兴,小子!\N{\fs48}Yeah, me too, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.94,0:00:39.10,SU,,0,0,0,,这种暴雪天气待在车里实在太冷了\N{\fs48}It's way too cold to stay in the van during this blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.10,0:00:41.37,SU,,0,0,0,,还有,车里的暖气也坏掉了\N{\fs48}Besides, the heater in the van hasn't worked
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.37,0:00:43.80,SU,,0,0,0,,大概是因为我装了那个迷你光碟播放器\N{\fs48}since I got that sweet mini-disc player installed,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.81,0:00:45.54,SU,,0,0,0,,可是我一点都不后悔\N{\fs48}which I do not regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.54,0:00:48.14,SU,,0,0,0,,我从来没有见过这么大的雪\N{\fs48}I've never seen it snow like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.14,0:00:50.28,SU,,0,0,0,,不完全对哦\N{\fs48}That's not entirely true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.28,0:00:52.21,SU,,0,0,0,,-怎么讲?-你是说那时候--\N{\fs48}-Really? -You mean back when --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.21,0:00:53.98,SU,,0,0,0,,哦!\N{\fs48}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.98,0:00:56.92,SU,,0,0,0,,那都是14年前事了!\N{\fs48}That was about 14 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.92,0:01:00.69,SU,,0,0,0,,当时有一场暴风雪,就像现在这样\N{\fs48}There was a snow storm happening just like this around then.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.69,0:01:02.39,SU,,0,0,0,,14年\N{\fs48}14 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.39,0:01:05.12,SU,,0,0,0,,嘿,我也是14岁!\N{\fs48}Hey, {\i1}I'm{\i} 14 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.13,0:01:07.56,SU,,0,0,0,,是啊,小家伙,当时你只有几个月大\N{\fs48}That's right, little man. You were only a few months old.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.56,0:01:09.46,SU,,0,0,0,,那时雪下得太大了\N{\fs48}And it was snowing so hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.46,0:01:11.50,SU,,0,0,0,,我以为我们俩会变成雪人\N{\fs48}I thought we were going to become Snowman
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.50,0:01:14.07,SU,,0,0,0,,还有雪人它儿子,雪人二世\N{\fs48}and Snowman Jr., son of Snowman.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.07,0:01:16.60,SU,,0,0,0,,刚好甜洋葱出城去看望家人\N{\fs48}But Vidalia was out of town visiting family,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.61,0:01:19.37,SU,,0,0,0,,所以她就让咱俩在她家住了一段时间\N{\fs48}so she let us crash at her place for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.38,0:01:20.77,SU,,0,0,0,,那是你第一次--\N{\fs48}It was the first time you --
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.78,0:01:22.18,SU,,0,0,0,,老爸!!\N{\fs48}Dad!!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.18,0:01:24.35,SU,,0,0,0,,我离你没那么远,史蒂文\N{\fs48}I'm not that far away, Steven.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.35,0:01:27.08,SU,,0,0,0,,别忘了咱俩的...约定\N{\fs48}Don't forget our... arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.08,0:01:28.54,SU,,0,0,0,,天了噜\N{\fs48}Good gravy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.54,0:01:31.39,SU,,0,0,0,,谁让你把我培养得喜欢音乐呢\N{\fs48}That's what you get for raising me to love music.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.39,0:01:35.72,SU,,0,0,0,,幸运的是,我正好有一首歌适合这个故事\N{\fs48}Luckily, I have a song for this story already.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.73,0:01:39.79,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪在我生命里,在我生命里♪\N{\fs48}♪ I could never be, I could never be ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.80,0:01:43.73,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪你的出现我措手不及♪\N{\fs48}♪ I could never be ready for this ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.73,0:01:47.77,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪我措手不及,我措手不及♪\N{\fs48}♪ I could never be, I could never be ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.77,0:01:51.57,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪遇见生命中的你♪\N{\fs48}♪ I could never be ready ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.57,0:01:54.84,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪开篇和结局♪\N{\fs48}♪ Things start, and things end ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.84,0:01:59.75,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪在理论里多么甜蜜,但♪\N{\fs48}♪ And isn't it lovely in theory, but ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.75,0:02:03.78,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪我措手不及,我措手不及♪\N{\fs48}♪ I could never be, I could never be ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.79,0:02:07.12,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪遇见生命中的你♪\N{\fs48}♪ I could never be ready ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.12,0:02:10.36,SUsong,,0,0,0,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.52,0:02:44.02,SU,,0,0,0,,嘿 小史嘟宝\N{\fs48}Hey, little Schtu-ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.03,0:02:46.16,SU,,0,0,0,,你在这儿跳什么舞呢\N{\fs48}You're doing a lot of dancing in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:49.96,SU,,0,0,0,,你想出来展示下舞步是吗\N{\fs48}You want to get out of there and show me your moves?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.96,0:02:53.80,SU,,0,0,0,,看看,你都把扣上的扣子弄开扣了\N{\fs48}Hey, now. You unbuttoned all your buttons I buttoned up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:02:58.44,SU,,0,0,0,,让我帮你扣上扣子\N{\fs48}Let's get you buttoned back up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.44,0:03:00.77,SU,,0,0,0,,马桑就吼\N{\fs48}Ookie-pookie!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:02.44,SU,,0,0,0,,好了!哈?\N{\fs48}There! Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:03.54,SU,,0,0,0,,干嘛...\N{\fs48}What's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.55,0:03:07.41,SU,,0,0,0,,你的宝石还需要呼吸是吗?\N{\fs48}Does your gem need to breathe?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.42,0:03:08.45,SU,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs48}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.45,0:03:11.09,SU,,0,0,0,,这样怎样?\N{\fs48}How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.42,0:03:16.29,SU,,0,0,0,,哦!呃,你们几个好啊!\N{\fs48}Oh! Um, hey, y'all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.29,0:03:18.69,SU,,0,0,0,,-你好!-唷,格雷格,瞧瞧这个!\N{\fs48}-Hello! -Yo, Greg, check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.69,0:03:20.73,SU,,0,0,0,,我们给小玫瑰带了礼物!\N{\fs48}We brought gifts for Lil' Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.73,0:03:23.26,SU,,0,0,0,,紫晶,我跟你说过的\N{\fs48}Amethyst, we've gone over this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.27,0:03:25.37,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文是个--\N{\fs48}Steven is a --
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.37,0:03:26.93,SU,,0,0,0,,人类宝宝\N{\fs48}Human baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.94,0:03:28.70,SU,,0,0,0,,还有史蒂文他...\N{\fs48}And Steven is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:30.44,SU,,0,0,0,,不是玫瑰\N{\fs48}Not Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.44,0:03:32.77,SU,,0,0,0,,你们需要点什么吗?\N{\fs48}Can I get you guys anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.78,0:03:36.94,SU,,0,0,0,,我这儿有水,有旧盘子,还有...\N{\fs48}We've got water, old plates, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.95,0:03:38.81,SU,,0,0,0,,来点茶怎样?\N{\fs48}How about some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.81,0:03:42.02,SU,,0,0,0,,不用。我们只是来放下这些礼物的\N{\fs48}No. We're just here to drop off these gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.02,0:03:44.08,SU,,0,0,0,,哦对!当然了\N{\fs48}Right! Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.09,0:03:45.39,SU,,0,0,0,,这个给你\N{\fs48}Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.82,0:03:49.06,SU,,0,0,0,,你可能得帮他拆开\N{\fs48}You'll probably have to open that up for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.06,0:03:50.22,SU,,0,0,0,,这个盒子\N{\fs48}It's just a box,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:52.56,SU,,0,0,0,,只是看起来像包装过了一样\N{\fs48}made to look like it's been carefully wrapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:03:58.60,SU,,0,0,0,,谢谢你,石榴,但是我不觉得他用得上这个\N{\fs48}Thanks, Garnet, but I don't think he needs this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.60,0:04:01.90,SU,,0,0,0,,哦,他会用得上的...在未来\N{\fs48}Oh, he'll need it... in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.77,0:04:05.07,SU,,0,0,0,,下一个是我的礼物!\N{\fs48}Let's open mine next!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.07,0:04:08.64,SU,,0,0,0,,哇!尿布!真是实用呢!\N{\fs48}Wow! Diapers! This is so practical!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:11.28,SU,,0,0,0,,等下 这些是成人纸尿布?!\N{\fs48}Wait. Are these adult diapers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:13.08,SU,,0,0,0,,对他来说太大了\N{\fs48}They're way too big for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.08,0:04:14.95,SU,,0,0,0,,那就告诉他把自己变得大一些!\N{\fs48}So tell him to make himself bigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.95,0:04:17.32,SU,,0,0,0,,你能做到对吧,小格雷格?\N{\fs48}You can do that, right, Lil' Greg?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.32,0:04:18.85,SU,,0,0,0,,你可以叫他史蒂文\N{\fs48}You can call him Steven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.85,0:04:21.82,SU,,0,0,0,,这是我和玫瑰最喜欢的名字\N{\fs48}That's the name Rose and I liked the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.82,0:04:24.26,SU,,0,0,0,,嘛,不管你叫他什么,他会用得到这个的\N{\fs48}Well, whatever you call him, he'll need this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.26,0:04:28.06,SU,,0,0,0,,呃,谢谢 这是什么儿童图书吗?\N{\fs48}Uh, thanks. This some kind of kid's book?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:29.83,SU,,0,0,0,,哦 是本词典\N{\fs48}Oh. A dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.83,0:04:31.87,SU,,0,0,0,,很显然,这是最好的礼物\N{\fs48}Obviously, it's the best gift
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:34.14,SU,,0,0,0,,最合适没有沟通能力的生物\N{\fs48}for a being that can't yet communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.14,0:04:37.37,SU,,0,0,0,,你们可以用它来查一下婴儿是什么意思\N{\fs48}Well, maybe you guys could use it to look up what a baby is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.37,0:04:38.77,SU,,0,0,0,,这些礼物都很棒\N{\fs48}These gifts are great,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.78,0:04:41.81,SU,,0,0,0,,但是史蒂文太小了用不到这些\N{\fs48}but Steven's just too young for this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.81,0:04:44.01,SU,,0,0,0,,现在,他最喜欢这个\N{\fs48}Nowadays, he's really into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:46.01,SU,,0,0,0,, ♪钥匙链 ♪\N{\fs48}♪ Carabiner ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.02,0:04:48.18,SU,,0,0,0,, ♪钥匙链!♪\N{\fs48}♪ Carabiner! ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:50.18,SU,,0,0,0,,哇!他真的喜欢!\N{\fs48}Whoa! He loves it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:52.92,SU,,0,0,0,,嘿,小-史蒂文!\N{\fs48}Hey, Lil' -- Steven!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.72,0:04:58.13,SU,,0,0,0,,嗯,他真的被这东西迷住了\N{\fs48}Hmm. He's certainly captivated with those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.13,0:04:59.66,SU,,0,0,0,,这样,下次我们就给他\N{\fs48}Well, next time, we'll just bring
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.66,0:05:01.40,SU,,0,0,0,,带一盒子钥匙就好了\N{\fs48}a big box of keys for Steven.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.34,0:05:09.04,SU,,0,0,0,,发生什么事了?!\N{\fs48}What's happening to him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.04,0:05:10.70,SU,,0,0,0,,是玫瑰I!\N{\fs48}t's Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.71,0:05:12.11,SU,,0,0,0,,这真的有可能吗?\N{\fs48}Is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:14.18,SU,,0,0,0,,他会变成一束激光吗?!\N{\fs48}Is he gonna turn into a laser?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.18,0:05:17.31,SU,,0,0,0,,放轻松,你们几个 我已经想明白了\N{\fs48}Relax, y'all. I got it all figured out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.31,0:05:20.61,SU,,0,0,0,,玫瑰正在试着变回原来的形态!\N{\fs48}Rose is trying to shape-shift back to her old self!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.62,0:05:23.35,SU,,0,0,0,,-啥?!-她现在变不回来\N{\fs48}-What?! -She can't shape-shift
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.35,0:05:25.52,SU,,0,0,0,,因为她被这个宝宝困住了!\N{\fs48}because she's trapped in a baby!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.52,0:05:26.89,SU,,0,0,0,,被宝宝困住?\N{\fs48}Trapped in a baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.89,0:05:28.22,SU,,0,0,0,,玫瑰?\N{\fs48}Rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.22,0:05:31.33,SU,,0,0,0,,玫瑰,是我,珍珠!你在里面吗?\N{\fs48}Rose, it's me. It's Pearl! Are you in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.33,0:05:33.49,SU,,0,0,0,,是的话就闪两下!\N{\fs48}Glow twice for yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:38.70,SU,,0,0,0,,宝宝别闹,我正试着和玫瑰说话呢\N{\fs48}Baby, please. I'm trying to talk to Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.70,0:05:42.10,SU,,0,0,0,,玫瑰没有变形,她也不是被困住\N{\fs48}Rose hasn't shape-shifted, and she isn't trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:44.80,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文是个融合体\N{\fs48}Steven is a fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.81,0:05:46.71,SU,,0,0,0,,玫瑰是在试着解开融合\N{\fs48}Rose could be trying to unfuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.71,0:05:49.14,SU,,0,0,0,,不管史蒂文是什么,现在有状况发生了\N{\fs48}Whatever Steven is, something's happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.15,0:05:51.98,SU,,0,0,0,,而我--我能帮上什么?!\N{\fs48}and I -- What can I do to help?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.98,0:05:54.95,SU,,0,0,0,,这个,人类婴儿发光的时候你都怎么处理啊?\N{\fs48}Well, what do you do with a human baby when it glows?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.95,0:05:58.42,SU,,0,0,0,,首先,人类婴儿不会发光\N{\fs48}First off, human babies don't glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.42,0:06:00.85,SU,,0,0,0,,然后其第二个次...\N{\fs48}And letter number "B"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.86,0:06:02.92,SU,,0,0,0,,要是会发光怎么办啊?!\N{\fs48}what if they do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:05.83,SU,,0,0,0,,不慌,甜洋葱那有些关于宝宝的书籍我有在读\N{\fs48}Okay, Vidalia has some books on babies I've been reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.83,0:06:08.93,SU,,0,0,0,,读书会给我们些头绪的\N{\fs48}They'll help us figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.77,0:06:12.07,SU,,0,0,0,,冷静,你能做到的\N{\fs48}Calm down. You got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.07,0:06:16.00,SU,,0,0,0,,各位,如果是类似发烧的症状的话,我们该--\N{\fs48}Guys, if this is anything like a fever, then we should --
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:18.54,SU,,0,0,0,,呃,人呢?\N{\fs48}Uh, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.54,0:06:19.87,SU,,0,0,0,,人呢?!\N{\fs48}Guys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.88,0:06:21.88,SU,,0,0,0,,你们拐走了我?!\N{\fs48}You kidnapped me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:23.11,SU,,0,0,0,,对头!\N{\fs48}Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:25.78,SU,,0,0,0,,我们有些行动确实有点令人后悔\N{\fs48}Some of our actions were a bit regrettable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.78,0:06:28.58,SU,,0,0,0,,当时,我们以为用自己的方式来解决\N{\fs48}At the time, we thought it'd be better
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.58,0:06:30.92,SU,,0,0,0,,会比较好一些\N{\fs48}to handle things our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.92,0:06:33.39,SU,,0,0,0,,管他呢 我们就直接拐了你\N{\fs48}Nah. We straight-up 'napped you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.36,0:06:38.36,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文!我的车!\N{\fs48}Steven! My van!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.36,0:06:40.96,SU,,0,0,0,,把宝宝还给我!\N{\fs48}Give me back my babies!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.96,0:06:42.23,SU,,0,0,0,,他看着很生气啊\N{\fs48}He looks mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.23,0:06:43.60,SU,,0,0,0,,他以后会感谢我们的\N{\fs48}He'll thank us later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.60,0:06:45.90,SU,,0,0,0,,格雷格一直以来都很努力\N{\fs48}Greg was doing his best up to this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.90,0:06:47.77,SU,,0,0,0,,但是现在情况变了\N{\fs48}But the situation has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.77,0:06:50.04,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文显然是个宝石人\N{\fs48}Steven is clearly a gem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.04,0:06:52.71,SU,,0,0,0,,还好我们没有解释就跑了\N{\fs48}Good thing we left without any explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.71,0:06:56.98,SU,,0,0,0,,好了,玫瑰,我们看到你发光了\N{\fs48}All right, Rose, we saw that glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.98,0:07:00.01,SU,,0,0,0,,所以你为什么还是个宝宝?\N{\fs48}So why are you still a baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.02,0:07:03.85,SU,,0,0,0,,是因为很有趣还是怎么的?\N{\fs48}Is it... really fun or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.85,0:07:07.52,SU,,0,0,0,,石榴,抱着我!\N{\fs48}Garnet, hold me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:08.72,SU,,0,0,0,,好吧,我懂你了\N{\fs48}All right, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.72,0:07:10.12,SU,,0,0,0,,这感觉简直太棒\N{\fs48} This rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.13,0:07:12.99,SU,,0,0,0,,但是你已经这样很长时间了--都几个月了!\N{\fs48}But it's been so long -- like months!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.00,0:07:15.53,SU,,0,0,0,,这比我变成马桶那次都长\N{\fs48}That's longer than I was a toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.53,0:07:16.90,SU,,0,0,0,,别这样,玫瑰!\N{\fs48}Come on, Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.90,0:07:19.53,SU,,0,0,0,,你该变回来了!\N{\fs48}You have to change back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.54,0:07:21.40,SU,,0,0,0,,宝宝 正常\N{\fs48}Baby. Normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.40,0:07:23.54,SU,,0,0,0,,宝宝 正常\N{\fs48}Baby. Normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.54,0:07:26.81,SU,,0,0,0,,宝宝...\N{\fs48}Baby...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.81,0:07:29.51,SU,,0,0,0,,这多容易啊!\N{\fs48}It's so easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.51,0:07:30.61,SU,,0,0,0,,为什么她就不肯变呢?\N{\fs48}Why can't she do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.61,0:07:33.08,SU,,0,0,0,,因为她不是在变形\N{\fs48}Because it's not shape-shifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.08,0:07:34.62,SU,,0,0,0,,她在融合\N{\fs48}It's fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.78,0:07:39.35,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文,我明白你的一部分是格雷格变的\N{\fs48}Steven, I understand Greg is part of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:41.79,SU,,0,0,0,,你不想在他面前解开融合\N{\fs48}and you don't want to unfuse in front of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.79,0:07:43.59,SU,,0,0,0,,因为会很不礼貌\N{\fs48}That would be very rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.59,0:07:45.29,SU,,0,0,0,,但是现在他没在这儿了\N{\fs48}But he's not here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.29,0:07:46.76,SU,,0,0,0,,就只有我们而已!\N{\fs48}It's just us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.76,0:07:48.60,SU,,0,0,0,,你可以休息一会儿了\N{\fs48}You can take a little break.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.60,0:07:50.80,SU,,0,0,0,,这样,我也来解开\N{\fs48}Here. I will, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.64,0:08:04.95,SU,,0,0,0,,我还在这儿!\N{\fs48}I'm here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.95,0:08:07.41,SU,,0,0,0,,你认识我的!你也认识她们!\N{\fs48}You know me! You know them, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.42,0:08:09.32,SU,,0,0,0,,我不明白!\N{\fs48}I don't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.65,0:08:14.25,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文!\N{\fs48}Steven!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:16.36,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文!\N{\fs48}Steven!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.36,0:08:19.36,SU,,0,0,0,,我该怎么追上她们?\N{\fs48}How am I gonna catch up with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.60,0:08:23.16,SU,,0,0,0,,狗\N{\fs48}Dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:24.33,SU,,0,0,0,,雪橇\N{\fs48}Sled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.33,0:08:26.30,SU,,0,0,0,,狗,雪橇\N{\fs48}Dog, sled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:29.00,SU,,0,0,0,,狗,雪橇\N{\fs48}Dog, sled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.01,0:08:31.24,SU,,0,0,0,,嘿!嘿,孩子们!\N{\fs48}Hey! Hey, you kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.31,0:08:35.11,SU,,0,0,0,,大家冷静下来\N{\fs48}Everyone, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.51,0:08:38.45,SU,,0,0,0,,看,我们都能看到她\N{\fs48}Look, we can all see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.45,0:08:40.35,SU,,0,0,0,,她就在这儿!\N{\fs48}She's right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.35,0:08:43.08,SU,,0,0,0,,她不能变形回来是因为\N{\fs48}She just can't reform because
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.09,0:08:46.49,SU,,0,0,0,,她被这个宝宝...包住了\N{\fs48}she has this... baby around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.49,0:08:48.99,SU,,0,0,0,,玫瑰,我知道你在里面\N{\fs48}Rose, I know you're in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.99,0:08:51.06,SU,,0,0,0,,我可以放你出来\N{\fs48}I can let you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.06,0:08:54.23,SU,,0,0,0,,我们能再次相聚\N{\fs48}We'll be together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.20,0:09:00.50,SU,,0,0,0,,我做不到\N{\fs48}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.50,0:09:01.84,SU,,0,0,0,,我做不到!\N{\fs48}I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.84,0:09:03.94,SU,,0,0,0,,她太想要这样了\N{\fs48}She wanted this so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.94,0:09:07.81,SU,,0,0,0,,我实在搞不懂为什么!\N{\fs48}I just don't understand why!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.11,0:09:11.44,SU,,0,0,0,,“万物都应生长,万物都应改变\N{\fs48}"Everything should grow, and everything should change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:12.88,SU,,0,0,0,,最--最棒的是\N{\fs48}And -- And isn't it so great
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.88,0:09:14.85,SU,,0,0,0,,这对于人类而言这多么自然”\N{\fs48}how it comes so naturally to humans."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:17.68,SU,,0,0,0,,这对于我们来说不自然啊!\N{\fs48}Well, it's not natural for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.89,0:09:22.26,SU,,0,0,0,,这对于我来说...不自然啊\N{\fs48}It's not natural...for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.26,0:09:23.72,SU,,0,0,0,,对他来说...\N{\fs48}It will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.73,0:09:25.83,SU,,0,0,0,,是自然的\N{\fs48}for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:30.70,SU,,0,0,0,,可是玫瑰呢?\N{\fs48}What about Rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:32.83,SU,,0,0,0,,这不是关于玫瑰的\N{\fs48}This isn't about Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.84,0:09:35.27,SU,,0,0,0,,从现在起,所有事都应该是关于\N{\fs48}From now on, everything has to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:37.47,SU,,0,0,0,,史蒂文的\N{\fs48}about Steven.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.67,0:09:42.38,SU,,0,0,0,,救---我!\N{\fs48}He-l-l-l-l-p!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.38,0:09:45.28,SU,,0,0,0,,救我!\N{\fs48}Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.28,0:09:46.68,SU,,0,0,0,,呃 谢谢\N{\fs48}Ugh. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.42,0:09:50.75,SU,,0,0,0,,嘿,等下!\N{\fs48}Hey, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.75,0:09:52.82,SU,,0,0,0,,你们为什么要在暴雪的天气\N{\fs48}Why did you take Steven on a joyride
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:54.62,SU,,0,0,0,,带史蒂文自驾游?\N{\fs48}in the middle of a blizzard?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.62,0:09:56.06,SU,,0,0,0,,你们这是要干什么啊?\N{\fs48}What's the big idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.06,0:09:58.93,SU,,0,0,0,,我们也没想好什么主意\N{\fs48}There wasn't really a big idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.93,0:10:01.70,SU,,0,0,0,,就是一些凑不到一起的零碎的想法\N{\fs48}Just a bunch of small ideas that never came together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.70,0:10:03.26,SU,,0,0,0,,是我的不对,格雷格\N{\fs48}My apologies, Greg.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.27,0:10:05.70,SU,,0,0,0,,我以为我们知道史蒂文是什么\N{\fs48}We thought we knew what Steven was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.70,0:10:06.97,SU,,0,0,0,,可是我们不知道\N{\fs48}But we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:09.30,SU,,0,0,0,,说实话,我也不确定我懂\N{\fs48}Honestly, I'm not sure if I do, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.30,0:10:12.44,SU,,0,0,0,,我从小时候起就没有发光过\N{\fs48}I never glowed when {\i1}I{\i} was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.44,0:10:15.31,SU,,0,0,0,,我们就没有小时候\N{\fs48}We never {\i1}were{\i} kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:19.71,SU,,0,0,0,,我不知道我们该怎么搞明白这些\N{\fs48}I don't know how we're going to figure this out,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.72,0:10:21.88,SU,,0,0,0,,但是我觉得如果我们一起来的话\N{\fs48}but I think we'll have a better shot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.88,0:10:24.15,SU,,0,0,0,,至少会更好一些\N{\fs48}if we do it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:33.29,SU,,0,0,0,,哇 你们几个真的搞错了所有事\N{\fs48}Wow. You guys were wrong about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.30,0:10:35.66,SU,,0,0,0,,这个,这件事已经--\N{\fs48}Well, that was a --
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:39.07,SU,,0,0,0,,过去了很长时间了,不是吗\N{\fs48}A really long time ago, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:40.47,SU,,0,0,0,,别对我们要求那么高,好不?\N{\fs48}Cut us some slack, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.47,0:10:43.60,SU,,0,0,0,,我们当时不知道该怎么做,甚至是我\N{\fs48}We couldn't have known what to do, even me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.61,0:10:45.11,SU,,0,0,0,,特别是我\N{\fs48}Especially me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.11,0:10:48.28,SU,,0,0,0,,不,我是说改变和成长\N{\fs48}No, I mean about changing and growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.28,0:10:50.64,SU,,0,0,0,,还有你对于你们来说不自然那些话?\N{\fs48}and how it doesn't come naturally to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.65,0:10:52.35,SU,,0,0,0,,但是看看你们现在的样子!\N{\fs48}But look at you now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.35,0:10:54.65,SU,,0,0,0,,我知道你们一直都在怀念妈妈\N{\fs48}I know you'll never stop missing Mom,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.65,0:10:57.35,SU,,0,0,0,,但是我想她会爱死现在这样的\N{\fs48}but I bet she would've loved this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.35,0:10:58.25,SU,,0,0,0,,我就是\N{\fs48}I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.25,0:10:59.75,SU,,0,0,0,,-同意-同意\N{\fs48}-Hear, hear. -Hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:01.49,SU,,0,0,0,,当时有个女孩绑架了史蒂文\N{\fs48}It wasn't such a big deal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.49,0:11:03.42,SU,,0,0,0,,那也不是什么大事对吧\N{\fs48}when that teenaged girl kidnapped Steven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:05.02,SU,,0,0,0,,那个是史蒂文的临时保姆\N{\fs48}That was his babysitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.03,0:11:06.66,SU,,0,0,0,,她带史蒂文去公园玩\N{\fs48}She took him to the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.66,0:11:09.90,SU,,0,0,0,,你们把攀爬架往她身上扔的时候真的把她吓到了\N{\fs48}You really scared her when you threw that jungle gym at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.60,0:11:19.64,SU,,0,0,0,,♪♪
